Custom theme support
  Allow users to define a complete colour scheme for vim-mdrender that
  overrides the default hi-link targets as a named unit, rather than
  having to override each MdXxx group individually.

  Proposed API:
    let g:mdrender_theme = 'dark'   " built-in named theme
    let g:mdrender_theme = {}       " inline dict of group → attrs

  Built-in themes to consider:
    'auto'    — current behaviour (links to colorscheme semantic groups)
    'dark'    — opinionated dark palette (One Dark-derived)
    'light'   — opinionated light palette
    'minimal' — style-only, no colour at all (bold/italic/underline only)

  Implementation notes:
    - Theme application should live in highlight.vim alongside Setup()
    - Must still respect user overrides (hi def so explicit hi wins)
    - Should re-apply on ColorScheme event like the rest of the highlight layer
